cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper deals with the detection of network anomalies using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of decision trees and random forests for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on Internet Protocol (IP) group and SNMP-MIB dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of machine learning for anomaly detection and intrusion detection systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
